<BODY>




<DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:right;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Exhibit 10.8</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:center;'><U><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>RESIGNATION AGREEMENT AND GENERAL RELEASE</font></B></U></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>This Resignation Agreement and General Release (hereinafter the &#147;Agreement&#148;) is offered to Tim Claydon (the &#147;Executive&#148;) this 16th day of January, 2007 by JetBlue Airways Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;).</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS, </font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'>the Executive desires to resign his employment with the Company as Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing on February 13, 2007 (the &#147;Resignation Date&#148;) and execute the resignation letter attached in Appendix A to this Agreement; and </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> the Company desires to retain the Executive as an employee in a Senior Advisor role through December 31, 2007 (&#147;Separation Date&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>NOW THEREFORE,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> in consideration of the mutual covenants and conditions set forth below, and intending to be legally bound thereby, the Company and the Executive covenant and agree as follows:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment and Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration for the Executive&#146;s obligations herein, the Company shall provide the following payments and benefits:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>a. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company shall continue to pay Executive his regular pay as of the Resignation Date for a normal payroll period, less all applicable withholdings from the Resignation Date through December 31, 2007 (the &#147;Advisory Role&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>b. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Bonus</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company shall pay Executive a bonus payment for 2006 in the amount that the Company may pay to its Senior Vice Presidents, if any, which shall be paid on or around the time the Company pays out bonus payments. The Executive specifically acknowledges and agrees that he will not eligible for a bonus for 2007.   </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>c. Executive will continue to receive profit sharing, if paid by the Company, for 2006 and 2007, to be paid in March 2007 and 2008, consecutively, into the Executive&#146;s Retirement Plan.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>d. The Company shall continue to make 401K matching contributions on behalf of the Executive during the Advisory Role. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>e. Executive&#146;s current stock options will continue to vest pursuant to the JetBlue Airways Corporation Stock Option Plan; provided, however, Executive shall not be eligible to receive any additional option grants as of February 13, 2007. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>f. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company agrees to continue the Executive&#146;s medical and dental benefits during the Advisory Role, subject to the terms and conditions of the plans. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>g. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Flight Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive and his immediate family shall be eligible for positive space flight benefits for the life of the Executive on JetBlue after the Separation Date, subject to the terms and conditions of the Company&#146;s pass travel programs and any future changes to those programs. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Other Payment or Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Except for payments and benefits provided for in Paragraph 1 of this Agreement, and those accrued but unused benefits to which the Executive is entitled, the Executive hereby acknowledges and agrees that the Executive is not entitled to any other compensation or benefits of any kind from the Company, including, but not limited to, any claims for salary, bonuses, severance, or any other payments or benefits whatsoever under any Company plan or program.  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Release</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration of the obligations of the Company herein, specifically the Executive&#146;s employment in the Advisory Role and the benefits described in Paragraph 1 of this Agreement to which the Executive acknowledges that the Executive is not otherwise entitled, the Executive hereby fully and forever unconditionally releases and discharges the Company and all of its past or present officers, directors, employees, insurers, agents, successors and assigns (hereinafter referred to collectively as the &#147;Releasees&#148;), from any and all manner of actions and causes of action, suits, debts, dues, accounts, bonds, covenants, contracts, agreements, judgments, charges, claims and demands whatsoever which the Executive, the Executive&#146;s heirs, executors, administrators and assigns has,
or may hereafter have against the Releasees arising out of or by reason of any cause, matter or thing whatsoever occurring on or before the date of this Agreement, including, but without limitation to, any or all matters relating to the Executive&#146;s employment by the Company and separation thereof, the Executive&#146;s benefits, and all matters arising under any international, federal, state, or local statute, rule or regulation or principle of contract law or common law, in law or in equity, including, but not limited to, claims arising under Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993, all as amended, and any other federal, state or local laws regarding employment discrimination, <u>excepting</u> only claims for worker&#146;s compensation, unemployment compensation and rights under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act
(&#147;COBRA&#148;). The Executive does not waive or release any rights arising after the Effective Date of this Agreement. Nothing in this Agreement and Release shall be construed to prevent Executive from filing a charge with, or participating in an investigation conducted by, the U.S. EEOC or applicable state agency, to the extent required or permitted by law. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>4. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Company Property</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive shall retain use of all Company property in the Executive&#146;s possession during the Advisory Period. At the end of the Advisory Period the Executive shall return all Company property. After giving effect to the return of the property discussed above, the Executive represents and warrants that the Executive has no Company records or copies of records or correspondence or copies of correspondence, other than non-confidential documents relating to the Executive&#146;s own employment by the Company. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>5. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Continuing Employment Duties</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. During the Advisory Role, the Company anticipates that the Executive will devote reasonable energies to his employment with the Company. The Executive acknowledges and agrees that during the Advisory Role he will not engage in any competitive business activity without the express written consent of the Company. Should the Executive obtain full-time employment with a competitor, the Executive acknowledges and agrees that the Advisory Period shall terminate and the Payments and Benefits in sections 1(a), (c), (d) and (f) shall cease immediately. The Executive must notify Vincent Stabile, Senior Vice President, People within 5 business days of obtaining full-time employment with a competitor.    </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>6. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Disparagement</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive agrees that the Executive will not publish or communicate to any person or entity Disparaging (as defined herein) remarks, comments or statements concerning the Releasees.  The Company shall inform its Officers, with knowledge of this Agreement, not publish or communicate to any person or entity any Disparaging remarks comments or statements concerning the Executive. &#147;Disparaging&#148; remarks, comments, or statements are those that impugn the character, honesty, integrity, morality, or business acumen or abilities in connection with any aspect of the operation of the Company&#146;s business or the Executive.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>7. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>References</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Any requests for references shall be directed to the Senior Vice President of People, Vincent Stabile. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>8. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Protection of Confidential Information</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive hereby acknowledges that the Executive remains subject to and agrees to abide by any and all existing duties and obligations respecting confidential and/or proprietary information of the Company.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>9. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Assignment of Rights</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive warrants that the Executive has not assigned or transferred any right or claim described in the general release given in Paragraph 3 above. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>10. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Voluntary and Knowing</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive represents and warrants that the Executive fully understands the terms of this Agreement and that the Executive knowingly and voluntarily, of the Executive&#146;s own free will without any duress, being fully informed, after due deliberation and after consultation with the Executive&#146;s own counsel, accepts its terms and signs the same as the Executive&#146;s own free act. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>11. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Exit Incentive</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The payments provided under this Agreement are not offered in connection with any specific exit incentive or other employment termination program.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>12. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Governing Law</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement shall be governed in all respects, whether as to validity, construction, capacity, and performance or otherwise by the laws of the State of  New York, no action involving this Agreement may be brought except in the State of New York</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>13. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Entire Agreement</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement constitutes the sole and entire agreement between the Company and the Executive and supersedes any and all understandings and agreements made prior hereto, if any.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>14. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Modification</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. No provision of this Agreement shall be amended, waived or modified except by an instrument in writing signed by the parties hereto.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>15. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Counterparts</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, both of which together shall constitute the original agreement. This Agreement may also be executed by facsimile signature.  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>16. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Admission of Liability</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. It is understood and agreed that the execution of this Agreement by the Company is not to be construed as an admission of any liability on its part to Executive other than to comply with the terms of this Agreement.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<div align=center>

        <td colspan="3" valign=bottom >
                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>ACCEPTED AND AGREED:</font></B></p> </td>
        <td valign=bottom >
                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p> </td>
        <td colspan="2" valign=bottom >
                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p> </td> </tr>
 <tr>
        <td colspan="3" valign=bottom >

                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Senior Vice President, People</font></p> </td> </tr></table>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>January 23, 2007</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Vincent Stabile </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Senior Vice President, People </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>JetBlue Airways Corporation </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>118-29 Queens Blvd.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Forest Hills, NY  11375 </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Dear Vinny,</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Effective February 13, 2007, I hereby resign my position as Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Sincerely,</font></p>



<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:28pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'><u>/s/ Tim Claydon&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u></font></p>

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-10.9
<SEQUENCE>4
<FILENAME>file4.htm
<DESCRIPTION>RESIGNATION AGREEMENT
<TEXT>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>




<DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:right;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Exhibit 10.9</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:16pt;text-align:center;'><U><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>RESIGNATION AGREEMENT AND GENERAL RELEASE</font></B></U></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>This Resignation Agreement and General Release (hereinafter the &#147;Agreement&#148;) is offered to Tom Anderson (the &#147;Executive&#148;) this 17th day of January, 2007 by JetBlue Airways Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;).</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> the Executive desires to resign his employment with the Company as Senior Vice President of Supply Chain and Aircraft Programs on February 13, 2007 (the &#147;Resignation Date&#148;) and execute the resignation letter attached in Appendix A to this Agreement; and </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS, </font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'>the Company desires to retain the Executive as an employee in a Senior Advisor role through December 31, 2007 (&#147;Separation Date&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>NOW THEREFORE</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'>, in consideration of the mutual covenants and conditions set forth below, and intending to be legally bound thereby, the Company and the Executive covenant and agree as follows:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment and Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration for the Executive&#146;s obligations herein, the Company shall provide the following payments and benefits:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>a. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>The Company shall continue to pay Executive his regular pay as of the Resignation Date for a normal payroll period, less all applicable withholdings from the Resignation Date through December 31, 2007 (the &#147;Advisory Role&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>b. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Bonus. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>The Company shall pay Executive a bonus payment for 2006 in the amount that the Company may pay to its Senior Vice Presidents, if any, which shall be paid on or around the time the Company pays out bonus payments. The Executive specifically acknowledges and agrees that he will not eligible for a bonus for 2007. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>c. Executive will continue to receive profit sharing, if paid by the Company, for 2006 and 2007, to be paid in March 2007 and 2008, consecutively, into the Executive&#146;s Retirement Plan.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>d. The Company shall continue to make 401K matching contributions on behalf of the Executive during the Advisory Role. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>e. Executive&#146;s current stock options will continue to vest pursuant to the JetBlue Airways Corporation Stock Option Plan; provided, however, Executive shall not be eligible to receive any additional option grants as of February 13, 2007. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>f. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company agrees to continue the Executive&#146;s medical and dental benefits during the Advisory Role, subject to the terms and conditions of the plans. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>g. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Flight Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive and his immediate family shall be eligible for positive space flight benefits for the life of the Executive on JetBlue after the Separation Date, subject to the terms and conditions of the Company&#146;s pass travel programs and any future changes to those programs. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Other Payment or Benefits.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> Except for payments and benefits provided for in Paragraph 1 of this Agreement, and those accrued but unused benefits to which the Executive is entitled, the Executive hereby acknowledges and agrees that the Executive is not entitled to any other compensation or benefits of any kind from the Company, including, but not limited to, any claims for salary, bonuses, severance, or any other payments or benefits whatsoever under any Company plan or program. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Release</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration of the obligations of the Company herein, specifically the Executive&#146;s employment in the Advisory Role and the benefits described in Paragraph</font><b><font style='font-size:10pt'> </font></b><font style='font-size:10pt'>1 of this Agreement to which the Executive acknowledges that the Executive is not otherwise entitled, the Executive hereby fully and forever unconditionally releases and discharges the Company and all of its past or present officers, directors, employees, insurers, agents, successors and assigns (hereinafter referred to collectively as the &#147;Releasees&#148;), from any and all manner of actions and causes of action, suits, debts, dues, accounts, bonds, covenants, contracts, agreements, judgments, charges, claims and demands whatsoever which the
Executive, the Executive&#146;s heirs, executors, administrators and assigns has, or may hereafter have against the Releasees arising out of or by reason of any cause, matter or thing whatsoever occurring on or before the date of this Agreement, including, but without limitation to, any or all matters relating to the Executive&#146;s employment by the Company and separation thereof, the Executive&#146;s benefits, and all matters arising under any international, federal, state, or local statute, rule or regulation or principle of contract law or common law, in law or in equity, including, but not limited to, claims arising under Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993, all as amended, and any other federal, state or local laws regarding employment discrimination, </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>excepting</font></u><font
style='font-size:10pt'> only claims for worker&#146;s compensation, unemployment compensation and rights under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (&#147;COBRA&#148;). The Executive does not waive or release any rights arising after the Effective Date of this Agreement. Nothing in this Agreement and Release shall be construed to prevent Executive from filing a charge with, or participating in an investigation conducted by, the U.S. EEOC or applicable state agency, to the extent required or permitted by law. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>4. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Company Property.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> The Executive shall retain use of all Company property in the Executive&#146;s possession during the Advisory Period. At the end of the Advisory Period the Executive shall return all Company property. After giving effect to the return of the property discussed above, the Executive represents and warrants that the Executive has no Company records or copies of records or correspondence or copies of correspondence, other than non-confidential documents relating to the Executive&#146;s own employment by the Company. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>5. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Continuing Employment Duties</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. During the Advisory Role, the Company anticipates that the Executive will devote reasonable energies to his employment with the Company. The Executive acknowledges and agrees that during the Advisory Role he will not engage in any competitive business activity without the express written consent of the Company. Should the Executive obtain full-time employment with a competitor, the Executive acknowledges and agrees that the Advisory Period shall terminate and the Payments and Benefits in sections 1(a), (c), (d) and (f) shall cease immediately. The Executive must notify Vincent Stabile, Senior Vice President, People within 5 business days of obtaining full-time employment with a competitor. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>6. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Disparagement.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> The Executive agrees that the Executive will not publish or communicate to any person or entity Disparaging (as defined herein) remarks, comments or statements concerning the Releasees. The Company shall inform its Officers, with knowledge of this Agreement, not publish or communicate to any person or entity any Disparaging remarks comments or statements concerning the Executive. &#147;Disparaging&#148; remarks, comments, or statements are those that impugn the character, honesty, integrity, morality, or business acumen or abilities in connection with any aspect of the operation of the Company&#146;s business or the Executive.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>7. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>References. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Any requests for references shall be directed to the Senior Vice President of People, Vincent Stabile. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>8. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Protection of Confidential Information</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive hereby acknowledges that the Executive remains subject to and agrees to abide by any and all existing duties and obligations respecting confidential and/or proprietary information of the Company.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>9. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Assignment of Rights</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive warrants that the Executive has not assigned or transferred any right or claim described in the general release given in Paragraph 3 above. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>10. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Voluntary and Knowing</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive represents and warrants that the Executive fully understands the terms of this Agreement and that the Executive knowingly and voluntarily, of the Executive&#146;s own free will without any duress, being fully informed, after due deliberation and after consultation with the Executive&#146;s own counsel, accepts its terms and signs the same as the Executive&#146;s own free act. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>11. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Exit Incentive</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The payments provided under this Agreement are not offered in connection with any specific exit incentive or other employment termination program.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>12. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Governing Law</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement shall be governed in all respects, whether as to validity, construction, capacity, and performance or otherwise by the laws of the State of New York, no action involving this Agreement may be brought except in the State of New York.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>13. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Entire Agreement</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement constitutes the sole and entire agreement between the Company and the Executive and supersedes any and all understandings and agreements made prior hereto, if any.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>14. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Modification</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. No provision of this Agreement shall be amended, waived or modified except by an instrument in writing signed by the parties hereto.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>15. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Counterparts.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, both of which together shall constitute the original agreement. This Agreement may also be executed by facsimile signature. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>16. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Admission of Liability</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. It is understood and agreed that the execution of this Agreement by the Company is not to be construed as an admission of any liability on its part to Executive other than to comply with the terms of this Agreement.</font></p>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>

            <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:8.0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Date: January 17, 2007 </font></p>
            <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:8.0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>/s/ TOM ANDERSON </font></p> </td>

                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>/s/ VINCENT STABILE</font> </p> </td> </tr>

                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Vincent Stabile</font></p> </td> </tr>

                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0pt;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Senior Vice President, People</font></p> </td> </tr></table>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>January 23, 2007</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Vincent Stabile </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Senior Vice President, People </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>JetBlue Airways Corporation </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>118-29 Queens Blvd.</font></p>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Dear Vinny,</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Effective February 13, 2007, I hereby resign my position as Senior Vice President of Supply Chain and Aircraft Programs. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Sincerely,</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'><u>/s/ TOM ANDERSON&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u></font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Tom Anderson </font></p>

<DESCRIPTION>RESIGNATION AGREEMENT

<TITLE>
</TITLE>

<BODY>




<DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:right;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Exhibit 10.10</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:16pt;text-align:center;'><U><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>AGREEMENT AND GENERAL RELEASE</font></B></U></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>This Agreement and General Release (hereinafter the &#147;Agreement&#148;) is offered to John Owen (the &#147;Executive&#148;) this 22<sup>nd</sup> day of January, 2007 by JetBlue Airways Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;).</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> the Executive desires to resign his employment with the Company as Executive Vice President and as trustee of the JetBlue Airways Corporation Retirement Plan on March 6, 2007  (the &#147;Resignation Date&#148;), whereon Executive&#146;s Employment Agreement, dated November 28, 1998 (&#147;Employment Agreement&#148;), shall terminate; and </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS, </font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'>the Company desires to retain the Executive as a Senior Advisor through December 31, 2008 (&#147;Separation Date&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>NOW THEREFORE</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'>, in consideration of the mutual covenants and conditions set forth below, and intending to be legally bound thereby, the Company and the Executive covenant and agree as follows:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Resignation</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive agrees to resign his employment with the Company as Executive Vice President of Supply Chain and IT and as trustee of the JetBlue Airways Corporation Retirement Plan by executing the resignation letter attached as Appendix A hereto, at which time his Employment Agreement shall terminate; provided, however, any continuing obligations set forth in that Employment Agreement, including, but not limited to, Section 5, Confidential Information and Covenant Not to Compete, shall survive. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment and Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration for the Executive&#146;s obligations herein, the Company shall provide the following payments and benefits:</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>a. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Payment.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> The Executive shall continue to receive his Base Salary, as set forth in his Employment Agreement, less all applicable withholdings and deductions, from the Resignation Date through December 31, 2008 (the &#147;Advisory Role&#148;). During the Advisory Role, Executive shall continue to be employed by the Company with duties to be mutually agreed upon by the parties. At the end of the Advisory Role, the Executive shall receive a lump sum payment of One Hundred and Fifty Thousand Dollars and No Cents ($150,000.00) subject to the Executive executing the Updated General Release attached as Appendix B to this Agreement (the &#147;Lump Sum Payment&#148;).  Such Lump Sum Payment shall be made within 15 business days of the Executive&#146;s execution of the Updated General Release attached as Appendix B.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>b. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Bonus. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>The Company shall pay Executive a bonus payment for 2006 of Seventy Five Thousand Dollars ($75,000) as set forth in Section 2.3 of his Employment Agreement. The bonus will be paid on or around March  15, 2007. The Executive specifically acknowledges and agrees that his employment during the Advisory Role will not be bonus eligible. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>c. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Profit Sharing</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>.  Executive will continue to receive profit sharing, if paid by the Company, for 2006, 2007 and 2008, to be paid in March 2007, 2008 and 2009 consecutively, into the Executive&#146;s retirement plan.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>d. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>401k</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company shall continue to make 401K matching contributions on behalf of the Executive during the Advisory Role. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>e. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Stock Options</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive&#146;s current stock options will continue to vest pursuant to the JetBlue Airways Corporation Stock Option Plan during the Advisory Role; however, Executive shall not be eligible to receive any additional option grants as of March 6, 2007. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>f. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Company agrees to continue the Executive&#146;s existing medical and dental benefits through the Advisory Role, subject to the terms and conditions of the plans. At the termination of the Advisory Role, the Company agrees to pay the Executive&#146;s COBRA premiums, on a monthly basis, for a period of 18 months, subject to the Executive executing the Updated Release Attached as Appendix B to this Agreement. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:10%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>g. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Flight Benefits</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive and his immediate family shall be eligible for unlimited positive space flight benefits for the life of the Executive on JetBlue, subject to the other terms and conditions of the Company&#146;s pass travel programs. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Other Payment or Benefits. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Except for the payments and benefits provided for in Paragraph 2 of this Agreement, and those accrued but unused benefits to which the Executive is entitled, the Executive hereby acknowledges and agrees that the Executive is not entitled to any other compensation or benefits of any kind from the Company, including, but not limited to, any claims for salary, bonuses, severance, or any other payments or benefits whatsoever under any Company plan or program.  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>4. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Release</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. In consideration of the obligations of the Company herein, specifically some of the payment and benefits described in Paragraph</font><b><font style='font-size:10pt'> </font></b><font style='font-size:10pt'>2 of this Agreement, some of which the Executive acknowledges that the Executive is not otherwise entitled, the Executive hereby fully and forever unconditionally releases and discharges the Company and all of its past or present officers, directors, employees, insurers, agents, subsidiaries, successors and assigns (hereinafter referred to collectively as the &#147;Releasees&#148;), from any and all manner of actions and causes of action, suits, debts, dues, accounts, bonds, covenants, contracts, agreements, judgments, charges, claims and demands whatsoever which the Executive, the
Executive&#146;s heirs, executors, administrators and assigns has, or may hereafter have against the Releasees arising out of or by reason of any cause, matter or thing whatsoever occurring on or before the Effective Date of this Agreement, including, but without limitation to, any or all matters relating to the Executive&#146;s employment by the Company and the separation thereof, the Executive&#146;s benefits, and all matters </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>arising under any international, federal, state, or local statute, rule or regulation or principle of contract law or common law, in law or in equity, including, but not limited to, claims arising under Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, the Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993, all as amended, and any other federal, state or local laws regarding employment discrimination, </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>excepting</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> only claims for worker&#146;s compensation, unemployment compensation and rights under the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (&#147;COBRA&#148;). The Executive does not waive or release any rights arising after the Effective Date of this Agreement. Nothing in this
Agreement and Release shall be construed to prevent Executive from filing a charge with, or participating in an investigation conducted by, the U.S. EEOC or applicable state agency, to the extent required or permitted by law or to prevent any challenge by the Executive to the waiver and release of any claim under the ADEA. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>5. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Compete</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>.  The parties agree that during the Advisory Role, if the Executive engages in Competitive Activity, which shall be defined as directly or indirectly owning, managing, operating, joining, controlling or participating in the ownership, management, operation or control of, or be employed by, any of the following air carriers:&nbsp; American Airlines, Delta Air Lines, US Airways, Northwest Airlines, United Air Lines, Continental Airlines, Southwest Airlines, Airtran Airways, Frontier Airlines, Spirit Airlines, Skybus and Virgin America (the &#147;Competitive Airlines&#148;), prior to May 1, 2007, the Advisory Role shall terminate, the Company&#146;s obligation to make and/or continue future Payments and Benefits as set forth in Paragraph 2(a), (b), (c), (d) and (f) of this Agreement shall
terminate, and the Executive shall be required to repay to the Company any Payments and Benefits paid to him pursuant to Paragraph 2(a), (b), (c), (d) and (f) of this Agreement within 3 business days of him engaging in the Competitive Activity. Should the Executive engage in Competitive Activity during the Advisory Role after May 1, 2007, the  Advisory Role shall terminate on the date he engages in Competitive Activity and the Company&#146;s obligation to make and/or continue future Payments and Benefits as set forth in Paragraph 2(a), (c), (d) and (f) of this Agreement shall terminate on the date he engages in Competitive Activity; except, however, the Lump Sum Payment set forth in Paragraph 2(a) shall be reduced to Seventy Five Thousand Dollars and No Cents ($75,000.00) and will be payable as set forth in Paragraph 2. The Executive must notify Vincent Stabile, Senior Vice President, People within 5 business days of engaging in Competitive Activity. &nbsp;Subject to the terms herein,
during the Advisory Role, the Executive shall not be precluded from working for any airline consulting firms (provided that the Executive may not be placed at a Competitive Airline or directly or indirectly perform full time duties for a Competitive Airline), freight carriers, airline investment banking firms, regional airlines, manufacturers, air taxi services, fractional jet operators, foreign airlines, and other similar companies.  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>6. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Company Property.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> The Executive shall retain use of all Company property in the Executive&#146;s possession during the Advisory Role. At the end of the Advisory Role the Executive shall return all Company property; provided, however, the Executive may purchase his laptop computer and cell phone at the book value of those items. The Executive represents and warrants that he will remove any and all confidential information regarding the Company and its </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>3</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>subsidiaries from his laptop computer. After giving effect to the return of the property discussed above, the Executive represents and warrants that the Executive has no Company records or copies of records or correspondence or copies of correspondence, other than non-confidential documents relating to the Executive&#146;s own employment by the Company. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>7. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Disparagement.</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> For a period of five years following the Resignation Date, the Executive agrees that the Executive will not publish or communicate to any person or entity Disparaging (as defined herein) remarks, comments or statements concerning the Releasees.  For a period of five years following the Resignation Date, the Company and its  Officers shall not publish or communicate to any person or entity any Disparaging remarks comments or statements concerning the Executive. &#147;Disparaging&#148; remarks, comments, or statements are those that impugn the character, honesty, integrity, morality, or business acumen or abilities in connection with any aspect of the operation of the Company&#146;s business or the Executive.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>8. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Protection of Confidential Information</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive hereby acknowledges that Executive remains subject to and agrees to abide by any and all existing duties and obligations respecting confidential and/or proprietary information of the Company.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>9. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Non-Assignment of Rights</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive warrants that the Executive has not assigned or transferred any right or claim described in the general release given in Paragraph 4 above. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>10. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Voluntary and Knowing</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The Executive represents and warrants that the Executive fully understands the terms of this Agreement and that the Executive knowingly and voluntarily, of the Executive&#146;s own free will without any duress, being fully informed, after due deliberation and after consultation with the Executive&#146;s own counsel, accepts its terms and signs the same as the Executive&#146;s own free act. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>11. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Revocation Period and Effective Date</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive acknowledges that the Company has provided the Executive the opportunity to review and consider this Agreement for at least twenty-one (21) days from the date the Company provided the Executive this Agreement. Executive represents that he was advised by the Company to review this Agreement with an attorney before signing. If Executive executes this Agreement prior to the expiration of twenty-one (21) days from the date the Company provided the Executive with this Agreement, the Executive voluntarily and knowingly waives any right the Executive may have, prior to signing this Agreement, to additional time within which to consider the Agreement. The Executive may revoke this Agreement within seven (7) days after he executes this Agreement by providing
written notification of the intended revocation to </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Vincent Stabile, Senior Vice President, People</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>, at the Company. This Agreement becomes effective on the eighth day after it is executed by both parties, provided that it is not revoked by the Executive prior to that date (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;).  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>12. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Exit Incentive</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. The payments provided under this Agreement are not offered in connection with any specific exit incentive or other employment termination program.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>4</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>13. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Governing Law</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement shall be governed in all respects, whether as to validity, construction, capacity, and performance or otherwise by the laws of the State of Connecticut.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>14. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Entire Agreement</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. This Agreement constitutes the sole and entire agreement between the Company and the Executive and supersedes any and all understandings and agreements made prior hereto, if any.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>15. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Modification</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. No provision of this Agreement shall be amended, waived or modified except by an instrument in writing signed by the parties hereto.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>16. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Counterparts. </font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, both of which together shall constitute the original agreement. This Agreement may also be executed by facsimile signature.  </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>17. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>No Admission of Liability</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. It is understood and agreed that the execution of this Agreement by the Company is not to be construed as an admission of any liability on its part to Executive other than to comply with the terms of this Agreement.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>ACCEPTED AND AGREED:</font></B></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Date: March 6, 2007 </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Dear Vinny,</font></p>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'><u>/s/ JOHN OWEN&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u><br>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:16pt;text-align:center;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>APPENDIX B</font></B></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:16pt;text-align:center;'><U><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>UPDATED RELEASE </font></B></U></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>This  Updated General Release (hereinafter the &#147;Release &#147;) is dated this ___ day of January, 2009__).</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> the Executive and the Company entered into an Agreement and General Release in March, 2007 (the &#147;2007 Agreement&#148;) whereby Executive resigned his employment with the Company as Executive Vice President and became employed as a Senior Advisor through December 31, 2008; and </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>WHEREAS,</font></B><font style='font-size:10pt'> the Executive desires to resign from his position as a Senior Advisor and terminate his employment with the Company.   </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>1. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Release</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Therefore, in consideration of the obligations of the Company set forth in the 2007 Agreement, to which the Executive acknowledges that the Executive is not otherwise entitled, the Executive hereby fully and forever unconditionally releases and discharges the Company and all of its past or present officers, directors, employees, insurers, agents, subsidiaries, successors and assigns (hereinafter referred to collectively as the &#147;Releasees&#148;), from any and all manner of actions and causes of action, suits, debts, dues, accounts, bonds, covenants, contracts, agreements, judgments, charges, claims and demands whatsoever which the Executive, the Executive&#146;s heirs, executors, administrators and assigns has, or may hereafter have against the Releasees arising out of or by reason of
any cause, matter or thing whatsoever occurring on or before the Effective Date of this Agreement, including, but without limitation to, any or all matters relating to the Executive&#146;s employment by the Company and the termination thereof, the Executive&#146;s benefits, and all matters arising under any international, federal, state, or local statute, rule or regulation or principle of contract law or common law, in law or in equity, including, but not limited to, claims arising under Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, the Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993, all as amended, and any other federal, state or local laws regarding employment discrimination, </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>excepting</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'> only claims for worker&#146;s compensation, unemployment compensation and rights under
the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (&#147;COBRA&#148;) and the obligations set forth in the 2007 Agreement. The Executive does not waive or release any rights arising after the Effective Date of this Release. Nothing in this Release shall be construed to prevent Executive from filing a charge with, or participating in an investigation conducted by, the U.S. EEOC or applicable state agency, to the extent required or permitted by law or to prevent any challenge by the Executive to the waiver and release of any claim under the ADEA. </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:center;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>7</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<!-- EEDocs PBStart--><hr noshade="noshade" align="center" width="100%" size="2"><p style='page-break-before:always'></p><DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<!-- EEDocs PBEnd-->

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt; text-indent:5%;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>2. </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'> Revocation Period and Effective Date</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>. Executive acknowledges that the Company has provided the Executive the opportunity to review and consider this Updated General Release Agreement for at least twenty-one (21) days from the date the Company provided the Executive this Release. Executive represents that he was advised by the Company to review this Release with an attorney before signing. If Executive executes this Release prior to the expiration of twenty-one (21) days from the date the Company provided the Executive with this Release, the Executive voluntarily and knowingly waives any right the Executive may have, prior to signing this Release, to additional time within which to consider the Release. The Executive may revoke this Release within seven (7) days after he executes this Release by
providing written notification of the intended revocation to </font><u><font style='font-size:10pt'>Vincent Stabile, Senior Vice President, People</font></u><font style='font-size:10pt'>, at the Company. This Release becomes effective on the eighth day after it is executed by both parties, provided that it is not revoked by the Executive prior to that date (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;). </font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:12pt;text-align:left;'><B><font STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>ACCEPTED AND AGREED:</font></B></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>Date: March 6, 2007 </font></p>

<DESCRIPTION>AMENDMENT NO. 4 TO PURCHASE AGREEMENT

<DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always;"></DIV><BR>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:3pt;text-align:right;'><B><font FACE="ARIAL" STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>EXECUTION COPY</font></B></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:3pt;text-align:right;'><b><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>Exhibit 10.17(d)</font></b></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:3pt;text-align:center;'><b><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>AMENDMENT No. 4 TO PURCHASE AGREEMENT DCT-025/2003</font></b></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>This Amendment No. 4 to Purchase Agreement DCT-025/2003 dated as of October 17, 2007 (&#147;Amendment 4&#148;) relates to the Purchase Agreement DCT-025/2003 (&#147;Purchase Agreement&#148;) between Embraer - Empresa Brasileira de Aeron&#225;utica S.A. (&#147;Embraer&#148;) and JetBlue Airways Corporation (&#147;Buyer&#148;) dated June 9, 2003 as amended from time to time (collectively referred to herein as &#147;Agreement&#148;). This Amendment 4 is between Embraer and Buyer, collectively referred to herein as the &#147;Parties&#148;.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>This Amendment 4 sets forth the further agreement between Embraer and Buyer relative to, among other things, delivery schedule modifications of Firm and Option Aircraft. All terms defined in the Purchase Agreement shall have the same meaning when used herein and in case of any conflict between this Amendment 4 and the Purchase Agreement, this Amendment 4 shall control.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>Now, therefore, for good and valuable consideration, which is hereby acknowledged, Embraer and Buyer hereby agree as follows:</font></p>
<div align=left>
<table border="0" cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style=' border-collapse:collapse;'>
 <tr>
        <td width="5%" valign=top style='padding:6.0pt 0in 0in 0in;'>
                        <p style=' margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;text-align:left;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;'><b><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>1.</font></b></p> </td>

</div>

<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:right;'><B><font FACE="ARIAL" STYLE='FONT-SIZE:10PT'>EXECUTION COPY</font></B><br><b><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>Exhibit 10.18(d)</font></b></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:center;'><b><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>AMENDMENT N&deg; 4 TO LETTER OF AGREEMENT DCT-026/2003</font></b></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt;text-align:left;'><font style='font-size:10pt'>&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'>This Amendment No. 4 to Letter of Agreement DCT-026/2003, dated as of October 17, 2007 (&#147;Amendment 4&#148;) relates to Letter Agreement DCT-026/2003 between Embraer - Empresa Brasileira de Aeron&#225;utica S.A. (&#147;Embraer&#148;) and JetBlue Airways Corporation (&#147;Buyer&#148;) dated June 9, 2003 as amended from time to time (collectively referred to herein as &#147;Letter Agreement&#148;). This Amendment 4 is between Embraer and Buyer, collectively referred to herein as the &#147;Parties&#148;.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'><a name="dv_m1"></a>This Amendment 4 sets forth the further agreement between Embraer and Buyer relative to [***] among other things. All capitalized terms used in this Amendment 4 and not defined herein, shall have the meaning given in the Purchase Agreement, and in case of any conflict between this Amendment 4, the Letter Agreement, the terms of this Amendment 4 shall control.</font></p>
<p style=' margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;text-align:left;'><font face="Arial" style='font-size:10pt'><a name="dv_m2"></a>Now, therefore, for good and valuable consideration, which is hereby acknowledged, Embraer and Buyer hereby agree as follows:</font></p>

<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; background-color: #ffffff">

</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">

</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">

</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">
<font style="opacity:100; position:relative; ">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report;</font>
</p>
<p style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;  width: 456pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; line-height: 12pt; padding-top:6pt; padding-left:0pt; padding-right:0pt; padding-bottom: 0pt; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 20pt; background-color: #ffffff">
<font style="opacity:100; position:relative; ">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The registrant&rsquo;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have:</font>
</p>

<td valign="top" style="font-family:serif;font-weight:normal;color:#000000;font-size: 10pt; padding-top: 6pt; padding-bottom: 6pt; text-align: left; font-style: normal; text-align: left;&#10;						width: 418pt;"><font style="opacity:100; position:relative; ">designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;</font></td>
